Preliminary Wrangling¶

The dataset consists of (183412, 20) columns and rows respectively.
It describes bike trips in Feb 2019 with some data about users including their birth year, user type and gender and some features abou the trip icluding duration and stations.

In [5]:
#To investigate in depth date and time facto we need to make some derived columns
for i in df[['start_time', 'end_time']]:
    df[i]=pd.to_datetime(df[i])
    df['{}'.format(i)+'_year'] = df[i].dt.year
    df['{}'.format(i)+'_month'] = df[i].dt.month
    df['{}'.format(i)+'_month_day'] = df[i].dt.day
    df['{}'.format(i)+'_day'] = df[i].dt.day_name()
    df['{}'.format(i)+'_hour'] = df[i].dt.hour

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset consists of (183412, 20) columns and rows respectively. It describes bike trips in Feb 2019 with some data about users including their birth year, user type and gender and some features abou the trip icluding duration and stations

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am intersted in investigating patterns of operations regarding duration and popular hours and days for hiring. I am also intersted in user ages and gender.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I'll make use of user columns, duration time & date columns

It's clear that 10 minutes trips are most common with gradual decrease in recurrence with increase of period.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. Were there features that strengthened each other in terms of looking at your feature(s) of interest?¶

We can find that females tend to have longer trips than males and subscribers tend to have longer trips than customers and the duration is longer for all in Saturdays and Sundays
Both men and women at all ages score long and short trips but longer trips are less likely to happen with members born after 1995 also elder members didn't score long trips.
Women at all ages participated in long trips.

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?¶

Very old people didn't have long trips and also the younger, middle aged did.
Females scored longer average duration of trips.
Night and doon hours till 7:00 am had the longest trips especially weekends, Tuesdays and Thursdays nights
